<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-10-25T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-10-25T07:00:00-05:00" n="464" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d464">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">832.00 Revolutions/148: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul at Bahia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Briggs</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Bahia</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-10-25T09:00:00-03:00">October 25, 1930—9
                                a.m.</date><lb/>[Received October 25—7:08 a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>A little trouble last night in downtown district but in general quiet,
                            and Coronel Ataliba Osorio in temporary control. <hi rend="italic">Pensacola</hi> arrived yesterday afternoon about 5 o’clock.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Briggs</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>